00:38:37.910 --> 00:38:39.860
of the system are performers.

00:38:39.860 --> 00:38:45.860
What they choose to view gets
presented on a larger screen,

00:38:45.860 --> 00:38:53.050
and they also get to see
how they're, like the cards

00:38:53.050 --> 00:38:56.290
that they choose, relate to
things that other users are

00:38:56.290 --> 00:38:56.920
choosing.

00:38:56.920 --> 00:38:59.710
And this adds like
a social element,

00:38:59.710 --> 00:39:04.450
a performative element,
and greatly changes

00:39:04.450 --> 00:39:11.560
the way users can see how
each of these different cards

00:39:11.560 --> 00:39:14.410
are, like they can actually
see more direct comparisons

00:39:14.410 --> 00:39:16.370
and [INAUDIBLE].

00:39:16.370 --> 00:39:19.110
So yeah, I [INAUDIBLE].

00:39:19.110 --> 00:39:20.820
PROFESSOR: No, no.

00:39:20.820 --> 00:39:23.970
Yeah, that's a
pretty powerful idea.

00:39:23.970 --> 00:39:28.710
I think that it's not just
a quantitative difference

00:39:28.710 --> 00:39:31.440
between different interfaces.

00:39:31.440 --> 00:39:36.060
Another example would be
the physical typewriter

00:39:36.060 --> 00:39:37.740
versus a word processor.

00:39:37.740 --> 00:39:41.940
It's not just that the word
processor makes it easier

00:39:41.940 --> 00:39:43.750
