00:39:43.750 --> 00:39:46.320
We actually write
different things.

00:39:46.320 --> 00:39:50.400
We think differently because
of this word processor

00:39:50.400 --> 00:39:53.760
working in a certain way
than we used to think

00:39:53.760 --> 00:39:55.470
when we had typewriters.

00:39:55.470 --> 00:39:59.640
It's somehow changed
the world, and not just,

00:39:59.640 --> 00:40:04.560
again, quantitatively,
but qualitatively.

00:40:04.560 --> 00:40:11.010
People understand
texts and themselves

00:40:11.010 --> 00:40:16.410
differently because of
this change of interface.

00:40:16.410 --> 00:40:20.670
And this is just an
extension of that,

00:40:20.670 --> 00:40:27.090
where we can understand
another data set completely

00:40:27.090 --> 00:40:31.740
differently, depending on how
it is, not just presented to us,

00:40:31.740 --> 00:40:34.290
but how we are allowed
to interact with it.

